Setting Up Locally ğŸ’»

1. Clone the repository
Clone this repository to your local machine using Git:

###
git clone <repository-url>
cd Step_Project_2
###

2. Install dependencies
If you want to run the application locally, first install the dependencies:

###
npm install
###

3. Running the app
You can start the app locally with:

###
node index.js
###
The application should now be running on the default port (or the one specified in the code). ğŸ‰

Running the Application with Docker ğŸ³
The repository includes a Dockerfile to containerize the application. To build and run it using Docker:

1. Build the Docker image:

###
docker build -t step-project-2 .
###

2. Run the Docker container:

###
docker run -p 3000:3000 step-project-2
###
The application will be available at http://localhost:3000. ğŸˆ

Running Tests ğŸ§ª
Unit tests for the application are located in the test/app.test.js file. To run the tests:

###
npm test
###
Jest (or the testing framework defined in package.json) will run the tests and show the results in your terminal. âœ…


